CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 24, 1945, pg. 8, reads: "Gorgeous Glamour Girls - This bevy of fashionable young women added plenty of dash and charm to the Beauty Shop Owners' Fashion Revue, Tuesday evening, in Schenley High School Auditorium. Smartly dressed from head to toe, they set the pace for styles in Easter Parade and summer sports wear.  Left photo, posing around the statue of Schenley High, are Katie B. Miller, Virginia Wooling and Leola Howard... - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Katie B. Miller, Virginia Wooling holding tennis racket, and Leola Howard, modeling sportswear for Beauty Shop Owners' Fashion Revue at Schenley High School
